to the editor re seoul may loosen its ties to the us front page dec 20 the results of the presidential election in south korea indicate that people in south korea want their government to continue in the pursuit of peace and reconciliation with north korea as initiated by the current president kim dae jung as an american citizen living in south korea i would urge the bush administration in washington to listen and cooperate not worrying so much about the loosening ties that were suggested by your report of the election and focusing instead on more positive efforts for peace in this part of the world dwight j strawn seoul south korea dec 20 2002

